First of all i am a student studying psych. and as much as u wanna blame the mother for not stepping in, there isn't much a family member can do. They can't shove the pills down his throat, they can't keep constant watch over him if he lives in his own apt. In the state of Pa ...if there is a person with a mental illness...no one can do shit about having him put into a hospital for treatment unless he is a threat to himself or others...that means he would have to goto the extent of trying to commit suicide, making threats about the government...and i'm being serious...it has to b like a huge threat to himself or others....walking down the street saying i'm gonna blow your head off ..won't get them into a hospital. So your points about his mother should have jumped in is invalid imo...most family members hands r tied in exactly what they can and can't do to help a family member with a mental illness.<br>
